resources.description:
Formex describes the format for the exchange of data between the Publication Office and its contractors. In particular (but not only), it defines the logical markup for documents which are published in the different series of the Offical Journal of the European Union. 

Formex V4 is based on the international standard XML (Extensible Markup Language — W3C Recommendation, February 10, 1998). It entered into force on May 1st, 2004. The specifications may however evolve in the course of time. The documentation only exists in English.
resources.name: Formex - Formalized Exchange of Electronic Publications

description:
The Official Journal of the European Union (OJ) is the official compendium of EU legislation (L series) and other official documents of the EU institutions, bodies and agencies (C series and its supplements). It is published every day from Tuesday to Saturday in the official languages of the EU and is available in different formats.

This collection contains the 2013 volume of the Official Journal (OJ) L and C series available in XML Formex format. The resources are grouped by language and available for bulk download.  

The Official Journal is also available in HTML and PDF format on the EUR-Lex website: http://eur-lex.europa.eu/homepage.html
title: Official Journals of the European Union - 2013
